The paper deals with biometric presentation attack detection, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The use of deep learning features also suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of a new capture device and the analysis of different features suggest a possible connection to image processing (cs.IR).
